      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A widely influential doctrine was introduced in the early 20th century by the Austrian architect Adolf Loos, arguing that ornament was a “crime” in that it was a waste of resources. This was a terrible mistake, failing to understand the real value played by ornament in the human environment, and leading to an era of stripped-down, ugly buildings. Worse, in Loos’ case it was borne of a racist doctrine, holding that Europeans were a superior race that, with their advanced mechanical technology, had outgrown the need for ornament.",
      "id": "15376200262057"
